            <p class="govuk-body">After the Secretary of State has made their decision, there is a 6 week period where people can challenge the decision in the High Court. This is called a Judicial Review.</p>
            
            <h2 class="govuk-heading-m" id="about-the-judicial-review">About the Judicial Review</h2>
            <p class="govuk-body">If you or another organisation decide to appeal against the Secretary of State's decision, you can ask for a Judicial Review. A judge will be appointed to hear your case in the High Court. The judge's decision will be final.</p>
